    shared/ui/main_window.ui
    ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
    Shared Qt Designer file consumed by BOTH:
      • Python  →  PySide6.QtUiTools.QUiLoader  (runtime load)
      • C++     →  AUTOUIC generates ui_main_window.h  (compile-time)

    FIX: contentsMargins now uses the correct <number> sub-elements
    (left/top/right/bottom) instead of <rect> (x/y/width/height).
    Qt 6.x uic rejects the <rect> form, producing:
        error: no matching function for call to
        'QVBoxLayout::setContentsMargins(QRect)'

    Open for visual editing:
        designer shared/ui/main_window.ui
    ════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
-->
